    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Description\n\nThe checkhealth command for vim.lsp seems to fail for me due to a faulty value in lua_ls.lua\n\nThe offending function is specifically check_enabled_configs, I've included a snippet below\n\n```lua\n      for k, v in\n        vim.spairs(config --[[@as table<string,any>]])\n      do\n        local v_str --- @type string?\n        if k == 'name' then\n          v_str = nil\n        elseif k == 'filetypes' or k == 'root_markers' then\n          v_str = table.concat(v, ', ') --  <--- Error thrown here\n        elseif type(v) == 'function' then\n          v_str = func_tostring(v)\n        else\n          v_str = vim.inspect(v, { newline = '\\n  ' })\n        end\n\n        if k == 'cmd' and type(v) == 'table' and vim.fn.executable(v[1]) == 0 then\n          report_warn((\"'%s' is not executable. Configuration will not be used.\"):format(v[1]))\n        end\n\n        if v_str then\n          text[#text + 1] = ('- %s: %s'):format(k, v_str)\n        end\n      end\n    end\n```\n\nNeovim version : \nNVIM v0.11.3\nBuild type: Release\nLuaJIT 2.1.1741730670\n\nSteps for reproduction : \n1. Run the specified Neovim version with nvim-lspconfig b80f82f59544f0770981b5a6c7d129ca276dab36\n2. Install lua_ls v3.18.2\n3. Launch Neovim and run :checkhealth vim.lsp\n4. See the error : \n\n```\n- ❌ ERROR Failed to run healthcheck for \"vim.lsp\" plugin. Exception:\n  ~/.local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/health.lua:202: invalid value (table) at index 1 in table for 'concat'\n```\n\nThis seems to result from nested tables being being included in root_markers for the table returned from lua_ls.\n\nThere seems to be a conditional trying to cover this case, but it seems off as I'm on nvim-0.11.3 and I still get the error\n\nHere's the conditional in question https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/b80f82f59544f0770981b5a6c7d129ca276dab36/lsp/lua_ls.lua#L86\n\nReplacing the conditional with the vim.list_extend expression right below it fixes the error.\n\nI'm just a user so I might be overlooking some detail. I would appreciate all input and comments and to see if a simple pull request can fix this.\n",
